docs.lead_paragraph: No doubt Wordsworth, as Paul Goodman remarks in your Speaking of Books (Jan. 12), tended to avoid the political. But we cannot, we must not, forget those rousing sections in "The Prelude" -- which, though published in 1850 after his death, record his residence in France and his youthful ardor for the French Revolution.

docs.lead_paragraph: This spring, it's back to the easy-going, nonchalant, American way of dressing. After a giddy, gaudy era in which clothes became costumes and wore people, fashion has rounded the bend to real. Spring clothes are beautiful -- soft, unconstructed enough to pack in a shoebox, yet classic enough to go anywhere.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE real professional basketball season starts this month. The championship playoffs, and the final jockeying for position before they begin, are what this sport is all about. The 82-game regular season for all National Basketball Association clubs is just a preliminary -- a neces sary and exhausting one -- to the entirely different, more intense, more exciting competition that begins this month.
